description: Naturenut helped some kids with a rubber worm for fishing and he no sooner tossed it in and caught this bad boy. Then released it.

Subject was caught in Lake Sherman. For those unfamiliar, it's name is a misnomer, as its mouth is proportionately pretty much the same size as the closely related largemouth bass. To differentiate the two, one should look at their scaling: the smallmouth bass is a lighter, more drab shade of green with vertical stripes going down its body. The largemouth is more evergreen in color and has a prominent, horizontal dark stripe going down its lateral line.

Visual similarities helped to determine the species M. salmoides
